    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-13T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">E.
                    W.</gloss>/7–1345: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 216 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]<note n="1" xml:id="d216fn1">For the full
                            text of this message, see <ref target="#d312">document No.
                            312</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-13T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 13, 1945—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7075. <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> has replied as follows to our
                        communications<note n="2" xml:id="d216fn2">See documents Nos. 190 and
                        303.</note>…:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>In view of the opinions expressed by the State <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                            >Dept</gloss> we have not as we had intended put our proposals<note
                            n="3" xml:id="d216fn3">Concerning the conclusion of peace treaties with
                                <persName corresp="#p_B5">Bulgaria</persName>, Hungary, and
                                <persName corresp="#p_R3">Rumania</persName>.</note> to the Soviet
                        Govt in advance <pb facs="0374" n="242" xml:id="pg_242"/> of the forthcoming
                        conference. We may, however, wish to put them forward at the conference.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
